Scrum/Agile suggests that teams do not track time spent, instead only tracking decreases (and increases) in time remaining for tasks.  The only workaround available is to enter dummy values in time spent which is confusing and irrelevant, much better to give us the option to force the entry of time spent data or not.  

This would be acceptable on a global basis, but it might be useful to have it on a per project/issuetype basis.

When importing a project from bugzilla cc: and qa: are imported as watchers. That's fine so far and works.

But if I have already imported some projects and now import another one, cc: and qa: are imported not only for the currently imported project, but also re-imported for all bugzilla projects from previous imports.

That's bad, because the watchers from previously imported projects might have been changed by the JIRA users and now are overwritten by the Bugzilla import -- even if you selected an import of a totally different bugzilla project.

In BugzillaImporterBean the method createWatchers has to be changed. Instead of 
{code}
Iterator bugzillaBugIdIter = previouslyImportedKeys.keySet().iterator();
{code}

it should be 

{code}
Iterator bugzillaBugIdIter = importedKeys.keySet().iterator();
{code}

so that only cc: and qa: of the currently imported project are imported as watchers and not for all previously imported projects.
P.S. I think there is the same problem with Bugzilla votes.

